wrote:

> Just to clarify - the "SamuraiWiki" is the new
> Japanese history
> "Wiki", which is to say it is the same software and
> is used the same
> as Wikipedia.  This also means that you do not have
> to create an
> account to do searches and read the information,
> etc.  Here is the
> main page:
> 
> http://wiki.samurai-archives.com/
> 
> You only need to sign up if you want to edit or add
> articles.  That's
> the only reason one would really need or want to
> sign up.  If you
> haven't taken a look at the SamuraiWiki yet, it is
> worth poking
> around. Some categories have hundreds of entries,
> others only 3 or 4.
> It's only been online for 2 months, so there is
> still a lot of work to
> go. Some categories that people here might find
> interesting could be
> the "Samurai" Category:
> 
>
http://wiki.samurai-archives.com/index.php?title=Category:Samurai
> 
> The "Bujutsu" Category:
> 
>
http://wiki.samurai-archives.com/index.php?title=Category:Bujutsu
> 
> "Battles":
> 
>
http://wiki.samurai-archives.com/index.php?title=Category:Battles
> 
> And so on. There are about 1100 articles up so far. 
> If you want to
> contribute, there are only 2 rules:
> 
> 1. Cite your sources.
> 2. If you plagarize from other sources, you will
> probably be banned
> without a warning.
> 
> 
>
